snippet.textDisplay: the method of the food processor, not kneading it and using as little water as possible is all about preventing gluten from being formed. They want to prevent gluten to keep it as crispy as possible (gluten creates chew). Because you're using gluten free flour you could just slap all those ingredients together, add more water to help you get it super thin and then it would get super crispy from being so thin.
snippet.textOriginal: the method of the food processor, not kneading it and using as little water as possible is all about preventing gluten from being formed.
